        new ResizeObserver(function (entries, observer) {
            entries.some(function (entry) {
                var contentRect = entry.contentRect;
                if (contentRect.width > 0 && contentRect.height > 0) {
                    requestAnimationFrame(function (now) {
                        window.wixFirstPaint = now;
                        dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('wixFirstPaint'));
                    });
                    observer.disconnect();
                    return true;
                }
            });
        }).observe(document.body);
    }
</script>

style="letter-spacing:normal;" class="wixui-rich-text__text"><span class="color_27 wixui-rich-text__text">Named after the fearless Amazonian queen, the Myrina Journal aims to shine light on women writers and artists in order to combat harmful societal norms, especially gender-based discrimination. The Myrina Journal hopes to provide a welcoming community for young feminists to share their opinions in the face of an irrationally prejudiced world. Run by students for students, our goal is to create a platform where gender is no longer an obstacle to being heard. By giving students who face gender oppression a voice, we are taking a powerful step to close the gender gap and create informed allies.</span></span></p>
